<h2>News &amp; Feature Articles</h2>


<p>
Following are news releases, features and updates about GISS research written by
NASA news services, GISS personnel, and affiliated offices.
(Page 2 of 14)</p><div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-clocks-july-2023-as-hottest-month-on-record-ever-since-1880">NASA Clocks July 2023 as Hottest Month on Record Ever Since 1880</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-clocks-july-2023-as-hottest-month-on-record-ever-since-1880"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202308_news_julytemps_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Map showing air temperatures across the Southwest U.S. on July 25, 2023" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>According to scientists at NASA’s Goddard Institute for Space Studies in New York, July 2023 was hotter than any other month in the global temperature record.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-08-14)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-clocks-july-2023-as-hottest-month-on-record-ever-since-1880">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/centers-and-facilities/ames/nasa-study-reveals-compounding-climate-risks-at-two-degrees-of-warming/">Study Reveals Compounding Climate Risks at 2 Degrees of Warming</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/centers-and-facilities/ames/nasa-study-reveals-compounding-climate-risks-at-two-degrees-of-warming/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202308_news_2degrees_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Global map of 'fire weather index' predicted for year 2045" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>If global temperatures keep rising and reach 2&#176;C above pre-industrial levels, people worldwide could face multiple impacts of climate change simultaneously.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-08-10)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/centers-and-facilities/ames/nasa-study-reveals-compounding-climate-risks-at-two-degrees-of-warming/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/science-research/planetary-science/astrobiology/nasa-selects-cross-divisional-teams-for-astrobiology-research/">NASA Selects Cross Divisional Teams for Astrobiology Research</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/science-research/planetary-science/astrobiology/nasa-selects-cross-divisional-teams-for-astrobiology-research/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202307_news_icar_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Artist's visualization of a possible surface and atmosphere of exoplanet Kepler 1649c" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
Michael Way of the Goddard Institute for Space Studies leads one of seven teams that are part of NASA's new Interdisciplinary Consortia for Astrobiology Research.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-07-26)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/science-research/planetary-science/astrobiology/nasa-selects-cross-divisional-teams-for-astrobiology-research/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/nasa-offers-many-resources-to-monitor-climate-change/">NASA Offers Many Resources to Monitor Climate Change</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/nasa-offers-many-resources-to-monitor-climate-change/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202307_news_monitor_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Image taken from space over the Pacific Ocean looking east across Baja California, the Sea of Cortez, and beyond" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
In light of recent extreme weather events in the United States and around the world, NASA held a media roundtable July 20 to highlight the agency's climate work. 
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-07-20)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/earth/nasa-offers-many-resources-to-monitor-climate-change/">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-finds-june-2023-hottest-on-record">NASA Finds June 2023 Hottest on Record</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-finds-june-2023-hottest-on-record"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202307_news_gistemp_1174x766.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Global map of June 2023 temperature anomalies, with large areas in dark red indicating temperatures 3 or more degrees Celsius warmer than the 1951-1980 baseline. Warm waters in the Pacific off South America show the developing El Ni&ntilde;o." /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
The Goddard Institute Surface Temperature Analysis (GISTEMP) found that June 2023 was 1.07°C above the 1951-1980 June baseline, the greatest such June anomaly measured.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-07-13)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-finds-june-2023-hottest-on-record">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/physical-oceanographer-studies-earths-ocean-and-climate">Romanou Leads Group Studying Interactions Between Oceans, Climate</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/physical-oceanographer-studies-earths-ocean-and-climate"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202306_feature_romanou_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Photo of Anastasia Romanou alongside a wall hanging of the NASA logo" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
To honor World Ocean Month and discover how NASA scientists are helping us better understand the world's oceans in a changing climate, NCCS interviewed GISS's Anastasia Romanou, who has developed and used some of the most advanced models of the complex Earth system.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-06-30)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/physical-oceanographer-studies-earths-ocean-and-climate">Go to NCCS Feature</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/impacts-of-air-pollution">Simulations Probe the Impacts of Air Pollution on Premature Deaths</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/impacts-of-air-pollution"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202304_feature_pollution_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Photo of very smoggy conditions in New Delhi, India" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
Models from GISS and Aarhus University were used to study the impact of air pollution on premature mortality under several emission and population scenarios.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-04-26)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nccs.nasa.gov/news-events/nccs-highlights/impacts-of-air-pollution">Go to NCCS Feature</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/best.html">GISS Scientists Select Best Institute Paper of 2022</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/best.html"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202304_pubs_best_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Image of journal paper first page" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
Scientists at NASA/GISS have voted the journal article “The Turning Point of the Aerosol Era” by Susanne E. Bauer et al. as the top work among the research publications by institute staff published in 2022.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-04-05)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://pubs.giss.nasa.gov/best.html">Read More</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="/research/briefs/2023_singh_01/">Hydroclimatic Impacts of Persistent Explosive Volcanism</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="/research/briefs/2023_singh_01/"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202303_brief_singh_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="International Space Station photo of the lower Nile River, Egypt and nearby locations" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
Persistent volcanism disrupted ancient Egyptian Society 2200 years ago. GISS scientists delve into this past event to understand why.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-03-27)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="/research/briefs/2023_singh_01/">Read Science Brief</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/goddard/2023/nasa-selects-scientific-support-for-goddard-institute-of-space-studies">NASA Selects Scientific Support for Goddard Institute for Space Studies</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/goddard/2023/nasa-selects-scientific-support-for-goddard-institute-of-space-studies"><img src="/gfx/spot/2017/201704_news_contract_1472x960.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Photo of NASA/GISS building" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
NASA has selected Autonomic Integra of Gaithersburg, Maryland, for specialized scientific support services to the Goddard Institute for Space Studies in New York.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-02-08)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/goddard/2023/nasa-selects-scientific-support-for-goddard-institute-of-space-studies">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-scientists-and-historian-named-aaas-2022-fellows">Dorothy Peteet One of Four NASA Staff Named AAAS Fellows</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-scientists-and-historian-named-aaas-2022-fellows"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202301_news_peteet_736x480.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Photo of Dorthy Peteet on a hiking trail overlooking the ocean" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
NASA/GISS's Dorothy Peteet is one of four individuals with NASA affiliations named 2022 fellows by the American Association for the Advancement of Science in recognition of their distinguished achievements in the scientific enterprise.<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-01-31)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/feature/goddard/2023/nasa-scientists-and-historian-named-aaas-2022-fellows">Go to NASA Release</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->



<div class="feature_simple">
<h2><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-says-2022-fifth-warmest-year-on-record-warming-trend-continues">NASA Says 2022 Fifth Warmest Year on Record</a></h2>
<div class="feature_img"><a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-says-2022-fifth-warmest-year-on-record-warming-trend-continues"><img src="/gfx/spot/2023/202301_news_gistemp_884x576.jpg" style="border:0" alt="Map of global 2018-2022 global temperature anomaly" /></a></div><!-- end feature_img -->
<div class="feature_txt"><p>
Earth's average surface temperature in 2022 tied with 2015 as the fifth warmest on record. Continuing the planet's long-term warming trend, global temperatures in 2022 were 1.6&#176;F above the 1951-1980 baseline.
<br />
<span class="feature_date">(2023-01-12)</span></p>
<p class="read">+ <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/press-release/nasa-says-2022-fifth-warmest-year-on-record-warming-trend-continues">Go to NASA Release</a><br \>+ <a href="https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/">Go to Dataset</a></p>
</div><!-- end feature_txt--></div><!-- end feature_simple -->






